### ModernLearn API Test File
### Use this with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api/v1

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:3000/health

### Get All Subjects
GET {{baseUrl}}/subjects

### Get All Topics
GET {{baseUrl}}/topics

### Get Topics by Subject ID (replace with actual ID after seeding)
GET {{baseUrl}}/topics?subjectId=YOUR_SUBJECT_ID

### Get Levels by Topic ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/levels?topicId=YOUR_TOPIC_ID

### Get Clusters
GET {{baseUrl}}/clusters?topicId=YOUR_TOPIC_ID&levelId=YOUR_LEVEL_ID

### Get Nodes by Cluster
GET {{baseUrl}}/nodes?clusterId=YOUR_CLUSTER_ID

### Create Subject (Admin - no auth required yet)
POST {{baseUrl}}/subjects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Computer Science",
  "description": "Fundamental concepts in computer science"
}

### Create Topic
POST {{baseUrl}}/topics
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "subjectId": "YOUR_SUBJECT_ID",
  "name": "Data Structures",
  "description": "Study of organizing and storing data",
  "learningGoals": [
    "Understand arrays, lists, and trees",
    "Implement common data structures",
    "Analyze time complexity"
  ]
}

### Get Current User (Requires Auth Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_FIREBASE_TOKEN

### Get Next Question (Requires Auth)
GET {{baseUrl}}/diagnostic/next-question?clusterId=YOUR_CLUSTER_ID
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_FIREBASE_TOKEN

### Submit Answer (Requires Auth)
POST {{baseUrl}}/diagnostic/submit-answer
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_FIREBASE_TOKEN
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "questionId": "YOUR_QUESTION_ID",
  "answer": "Your answer here",
  "clusterId": "YOUR_CLUSTER_ID"
}
